### ============================================================
### Notebook Ops Platform - Serverless API Testing
### ============================================================
###
### Use this file with VS Code REST Client.
### Targets AWS API Gateway + Lambda endpoints in terraform/batch-dev.
###
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = https://n69rb6bzvl.execute-api.eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/dev
@apiKey = your_api_gateway_key_here
@jobId = your_job_id_here

### ============================================================
### 1. Submit Job (POST /batch/jobs)
### ============================================================
### Notes:
### - Include one .ipynb notebook part named `notebook`
### - Include param_* scalar fields
### - Include execution_profile: standard | ec2_200gb
### - Include optional data file parts

POST {{baseUrl}}/batch/jobs
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----BoundaryNotebookUpload

------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="notebook"; filename="Data_cleaning.ipynb"
Content-Type: application/x-ipynb+json

< ../demo_input/Data_cleaning.ipynb
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="upload_01"; filename="Template_MBO_Example_raw_v3.xlsx"
Content-Type: application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.spreadsheetml.sheet

< ../demo_input/Template_MBO_Example_raw_v3.xlsx
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="param_01_input_data_filename"

Template_MBO_Example_raw_v3.xlsx
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="param_02_input_data_sheet"

BIRDS
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="param_03_input_metadata_sheet"

METADATA
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="param_04_output_samples_ecological_parameters"

false
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="param_05_output_make_plots"

true
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="param_07_first_month"

1
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="param_10_upper_limit_max_depth"

0
------BoundaryNotebookUpload
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="execution_profile"

standard
------BoundaryNotebookUpload--

### Expected response body shape:
### {
###   "message": "Job successfully mapped and submitted",
###   "job_id": "...",
###   "batch_job_id": "...",
###   "execution_profile": "standard"
### }

### ============================================================
### 2. Check Job Status (GET /batch/jobs/{job_id})
### ============================================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/batch/jobs/{{jobId}}
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

### ============================================================
### 3. Fetch Job Logs (GET /batch/jobs/{job_id}/logs)
### ============================================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/batch/jobs/{{jobId}}/logs
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

### ============================================================
### 4. Fetch Job Results (GET /batch/jobs/{job_id}/results)
### ============================================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/batch/jobs/{{jobId}}/results
x-api-key: {{apiKey}}

### ============================================================
### 5. Optional CORS preflight check (if enabled in API Gateway)
### ============================================================

OPTIONS {{baseUrl}}/batch/jobs
Origin: http://localhost:5173
Access-Control-Request-Method: POST
Access-Control-Request-Headers: x-api-key,content-type
